    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T11:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T11:32:00-05:00" n="146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <head>146. Telegram From the Commander in Chief, Atlantic (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DARL1" type="from">Dennison</persName>) to the Commander of
                    Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="to"
                        >Clark</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d146fn0">Source: Naval
                        Historical Center, Area Files, Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Emergency;
                        Exclusive. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Norfolk</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-04-19T11:32:00-05:00">April 19, 1961, 11:32 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191632Z. Bumpy Road. Exclusive for RAdm <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                        >Clark</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gen Gray</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Provide continuous air cover over beaches today to protect <gloss
                            target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> from air attack.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Protection from ground attack not authorized.<note n="1" xml:id="d146fn1"
                            >At 11:31 a.m., <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> reported
                            to <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName> that he had received
                            the following message from Blue Beach: “Out of ammunition. Men fighting
                            in water. If no help given Blue Beach lost.” (<gloss target="#t_CTG1"
                                >CTG</gloss> 81.8 telegram 191631Z to <gloss
                                target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss>, April 19;
                            ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
